\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Unclamped $\beta ^*$ as a function of ensemble size $N_e$ on Lorenz~96, by target. Log scale. The identity target produces $\beta ^*$ in the $10^8$--$10^9$ range and the scaled identity in the $10^3$--$10^5$ range, both far outside the valid $[0,1]$ interval and clamped at every cycle. The eigenvalue target sits at $\beta ^* \approx 10^{-4}$, effectively no shrinkage. Cosmological target excluded (not defined for Lorenz~96).}}{13}{figure.1.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:beta_vs_ne}{{3}{13}{Unclamped $\beta ^*$ as a function of ensemble size $N_e$ on Lorenz~96, by target. Log scale. The identity target produces $\beta ^*$ in the $10^8$--$10^9$ range and the scaled identity in the $10^3$--$10^5$ range, both far outside the valid $[0,1]$ interval and clamped at every cycle. The eigenvalue target sits at $\beta ^* \approx 10^{-4}$, effectively no shrinkage. Cosmological target excluded (not defined for Lorenz~96)}{figure.1.3}{}}
