\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {9}{\ignorespaces Regime map for shrinkage-based EnKF precision estimation. Horizontal axis: concentration ratio $n/N_e$. Vertical axis: structural distance from the shrinkage target (e.g.\ off-diagonal energy of the true precision relative to a diagonal target). The two test domains of this work occupy opposite quadrants: BOSS cosmological data is near-diagonal (low vertical), Lorenz~96 is dense (high vertical). The recommended method changes across the map; see text.}}{20}{figure.1.9}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:regime_map}{{9}{20}{Regime map for shrinkage-based EnKF precision estimation. Horizontal axis: concentration ratio $n/N_e$. Vertical axis: structural distance from the shrinkage target (e.g.\ off-diagonal energy of the true precision relative to a diagonal target). The two test domains of this work occupy opposite quadrants: BOSS cosmological data is near-diagonal (low vertical), Lorenz~96 is dense (high vertical). The recommended method changes across the map; see text}{figure.1.9}{}}
